ps://www.virtus.sport/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Box_2013-New-Caledonia.pdf|title=Results - INAS World Swimming Championships 2013|last=|first=|date=23 August 2013|website=virtus.sport|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017 || {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Aguascalientes]] || 29 November - 3 December || || ||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.virtus.sport/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Box_2017-Mexico.pdf|title=2017 INAS Swimming Championship Results|last=|first=|date=14 December 2017|website=virtus.sport|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Medal table==\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | flag_template  = \n | event          = \n | team           = \n | gold_AUS = 50 | silver_AUS = 41 | bronze_AUS = 36\n | gold_HKG = 41 | silver_HKG = 30 | bronze_HKG = 24\n | gold_GBR = 21 | silver_GBR = 33 | bronze_GBR = 27\n | gold_BRA = 20 | silver_BRA = 7 | bronze_BRA = 5\n | gold_HUN = 17 | silver_HUN = 8 | bronze_HUN = 10\n | gold_SWE = 15 | silver_SWE = 12 | bronze_SWE = 14\n | gold_ISL = 15 | silver_ISL = 10 | bronze_ISL = 7\n | gold_JPN = 14 | silver_JPN = 23 | bronze_JPN = 20\n | gold_MEX = 10 | silver_MEX = 12 | bronze_MEX = 13\n | gold_RSA = 9 | silver_RSA = 21 | bronze_RSA = 26\n | gold_FRA = 9 | silver_FRA = 8 | bronze_FRA = 5\n | gold_ESP = 8 | silver_ESP = 9 | bronze_ESP = 3\n | gold_NED = 7 | silver_NED = 3 | bronze_NED = 3\n | gold_POL = 3 | silver_POL = 6 | bronze_POL = 10\n | gold_TPE = 2 | silver_TPE = 4 | bronze_TPE = 2\n | gold_EST = 2 | silver_EST = 3 | bronze_EST = 4\n | gold_KOR = 2 | silver_KOR = 2 | bronze_KOR = 4\n | gold_USA = 1 | silver_USA = 5 | bronze_USA = 7\n | gold_COL = 1 | silver_COL = 4 | bronze_COL = 4\n | gold_MAC = 1 | silver_MAC = 1 | bronze_MAC = 1\n | gold_CZE = 0 | silver_CZE = 4 | bronze_CZE = 6\n | gold_BEL = 0 | silver_BEL = 0 | bronze_BEL = 3\n | gold_DEN = 0 | silver_DEN = 0 | bronze_DEN = 1\n | gold_RUS = 0 | silver_RUS = 0 | bronze_RUS = 1\n}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[World Para Swimming Championships]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{International swimming}}\n\n[[Category:Paralympic swimming]]\n[[Category:Disabled sports competitions]]\n", "text_old": "'''INAS World Swimming Championships''' are a quadrennial international [[swimming]] competition organised by [[International Sports Federation for Persons with Intellectual Disability]] for athletes who have an [[intellectual impairment]] and swim in the [[S14 (classification)|S14 swimming category]] in [[Paralympic swimming]].\n\n==Swimming events contested==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Event !! 1989 !! 2004 !! 2005 !! 2007 !! 2009 !! 2013 !! 2017\n|-\n|align=left|50m [[freestyle (swimming)|freestyle]] || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|100m freestyle || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|200m freestyle || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|400m freestyle || || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|800m freestyle || || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|1500m freestyle || || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|50m [[backstroke]] || X || X || X || X || X || X || X \n|-\n|align=left|100m backstroke || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|200m backstroke || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|50m [[breaststroke]] || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|100m breaststroke || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|200m breaststroke || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|50m [[butterfly stroke|butterfly]] || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|100m butterfly || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|200m butterfly || || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|200m [[individual medley]] || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|400m individual medley || || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|4x50m freestyle relay || X || X || X || X || X || X || X\n|-\n|align=left|4